What is the least possible value of $(x y-1)^{2}+(x+y)^{2}$ for real numbers $x$ and $y$?
(A) 0
(B) \frac{1}{4}
(C) \frac{1}{2}
(D) 1
(E) 2

The real numbers $c, b, a$ form an arithmetic sequence with $a \geq b \geq c \geq 0$. The quadratic $a x^{2}+b x+c$ has exactly one root. What is this root?
(A) -7-4 \sqrt{3}
(B) -2-\sqrt{3}
(C) -1
(D) -2+\sqrt{3}
(E) -7+4 \sqrt{3}
